<HEADLINE>
FIRST NATIONAL MUSIC CARE CONFERENCE HELD IN KAOHSIUNG
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kaohsiung,   March  28  (CNA) 03/28/07  16:46:03 (By Elizabeth
Hsu)
</P>
<P>
The first national music care conference in Taiwan opened
Wednesday in the southern city of Kaohsiung, attended by
representatives of hospitals, clinics, other health-care
facilities, social welfare organizations and homes for the
elderly from around the country.
</P>
<P>
The event comprises panel discussions on music care theory and
demonstration workshops for the attendees to share innovative
health care skills, knowledge and the therapeutic effects of
music.
</P>
<P>
Music therapy has become more and more popular after a Japanese
music care expert introduced the practice into Taiwan in 1999 to
help thousands of victims of the Sept. 21, 1999 earthquake.
</P>
